  "text": "Ϫ/Ϫ (P ϭ 0.03), and AS160 Ϫ/Ϫ /Tbc1d1 Ϫ/Ϫ mice (P ϭ 0.02). Bar graphs above curves show areas under the curve (AUC). Glucose tolerance tests were also performed with 2 mg glucose/g body wt, as in Ref. [CITATION_1] . Similar abnormalities were observed, as shown for male and female mice, but several of the BG levels were above the reading range of the glucometer (Ͼ600 mg/dl). B: insulin tolerance tests were performed at 2 PM on 10-wk-old random-fed male (left) and female (right) WT (n ϭ 6 -8), AS160 Ϫ/Ϫ (n ϭ 5), Tbc1d1 Ϫ/Ϫ (n ϭ 5-6), and AS160 Ϫ/Ϫ /Tbc1d1 Ϫ/Ϫ (n ϭ 6 -7) mice. For the description of symbols and lines for different genotypes, see A. BG levels were measured before (time 0) and after an intraperitoneal injection of insulin (0.75 U/kg body wt) at 15, 30, 45, and 60 min. BG in %BG at time 0 [BG (%basal)] (means Ϯ SE) is graphed. Data were analyzed by 2-way ANOVA. For male mice, data are statistically significantly different from WT for male AS160 Ϫ/Ϫ /Tbc1d1 Ϫ/Ϫ (P Ͻ 0.0001) and AS160 Ϫ/Ϫ mice (P ϭ 0.0002), but not for Tbc1d1 Ϫ/Ϫ mice (P ϭ 0.47). Data are statistically significantly different from Tbc1d1 Ϫ/Ϫ mice for AS160 Ϫ/Ϫ (P ϭ 0.03) and AS160 Ϫ/Ϫ /Tbc1d1 Ϫ/Ϫ mice (P ϭ 0.0004), but there was no difference between AS160 Ϫ/Ϫ and AS160 Ϫ/Ϫ /Tbc1d1 Ϫ/Ϫ mice (P ϭ 0.18). For females, data are statistically significantly different from WT for AS160 Ϫ/Ϫ /Tbc1d1 Ϫ/Ϫ (P ϭ 0.0007) and AS160",
